@startuml Agent-to-Agent Protocol Specification
!include <C4/C4_Component>

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center

title Healthcare Insurance Multi-Agent AI Platform\nAgent-to-Agent (A2A) Communication Protocol\n(Secure, Observable, Governed Message Exchange)

participant "Clinical Agent\n(Requester)" as Clinical
participant "Agent Gateway\n(Registry + Router)" as Gateway
participant "Benefits Agent\n(Provider)" as Benefits
participant "Observability\n(Tracing)" as Observability
participant "Audit Log\n(Compliance)" as Audit

== Agent Discovery Phase ==

Clinical -> Gateway : **1. Discovery Request**\n"Which agent handles benefits?"
note right of Clinical
  **Discovery Query:**
  {
    "capability": "validate_coverage",
    "service_type": "benefits",
    "version": "v2.x"
  }
end note

Gateway -> Gateway : Query Agent Registry
note right of Gateway
  **Agent Registry Query:**
  
  SELECT agent_id, endpoints, version, status
  FROM agent_registry
  WHERE capability LIKE '%validate_coverage%'
    AND status = 'ACTIVE'
    AND version >= 'v2.0'
  
  **Result:**
  {
    "agent_id": "benefits-agent",
    "replicas": [
      "benefits-agent-0.healthcare-prod.svc",
      "benefits-agent-1.healthcare-prod.svc",
      "benefits-agent-2.healthcare-prod.svc"
    ],
    "version": "v2.1.0",
    "status": "HEALTHY",
    "load": [60%, 45%, 70%]
  }
end note

Gateway --> Clinical : **2. Discovery Response**\nbenefits-agent (replica-1)
note left of Gateway
  **Load Balancing Decision:**
  • replica-0: 60% load
  • replica-1: 45% load ✓ Selected
  • replica-2: 70% load
  
  **Selection:** Least loaded replica
end note

== Message Preparation Phase ==

Clinical -> Clinical : Prepare A2A Message
note right of Clinical
  **A2A Message Structure:**
  {
    "message_id": "msg-abc-123",
    "correlation_id": "PA-2026-001234",
    "source_agent": {
      "agent_id": "clinical-agent",
      "instance_id": "clinical-agent-5",
      "version": "v2.3.1"
    },
    "target_agent": {
      "agent_id": "benefits-agent",
      "instance_id": "benefits-agent-1"
    },
    "message_type": "REQUEST",
    "priority": "NORMAL",
    "timestamp": "2026-06-01T10:30:00Z",
    "ttl_ms": 30000,
    
    "payload": {
      "task": "validate_coverage",
      "member_id": "M123456",
      "service_codes": ["97110", "97140"],
      "service_date": "2026-06-15",
      "provider_npi": "1234567890"
    },
    
    "security": {
      "signed": true,
      "signature": "SHA256-RSA...",
      "jwt_token": "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIs...",
      "tenant_id": "payer-a"
    },
    
    "observability": {
      "trace_id": "trace-xyz-789",
      "span_id": "span-001",
      "parent_span_id": "span-supervisor"
    },
    
    "sla": {
      "timeout_ms": 5000,
      "retry_policy": "exponential_backoff",
      "max_retries": 3
    },
    
    "schema_version": "v2.0"
  }
  
  **Message Size:** ~2KB
end note

== Authentication & Authorization Phase ==

Clinical -> Gateway : **3. Send A2A Request**\n(with JWT token)

Gateway -> Gateway : Validate JWT Token
note right of Gateway
  **JWT Validation:**
  • Signature verification (RS256)
  • Expiration check
  • Issuer validation
  • Audience validation
  • Custom claims check
  
  **JWT Claims:**
  {
    "sub": "clinical-agent",
    "iss": "https://healthcare-auth",
    "aud": "agent-mesh",
    "exp": 1717241400,
    "iat": 1717238000,
    "roles": ["clinical_reviewer"],
    "permissions": [
      "call:benefits-agent",
      "read:member_data"
    ]
  }
end note

Gateway -> Gateway : Check RBAC Policy
note right of Gateway
  **OPA Policy Evaluation:**
  
  ```rego
  allow {
    input.source == "clinical-agent"
    input.target == "benefits-agent"
    input.action == "validate_coverage"
    "call:benefits-agent" in input.permissions
  }
  ```
  
  **Result:** ALLOW ✓
end note

== Schema Validation Phase ==

Gateway -> Gateway : Validate Message Schema
note right of Gateway
  **JSON Schema Validation:**
  
  Required fields:
  ✓ message_id
  ✓ source_agent
  ✓ target_agent
  ✓ message_type
  ✓ payload
  ✓ security.jwt_token
  ✓ observability.trace_id
  
  Payload schema (validate_coverage):
  ✓ member_id: string
  ✓ service_codes: array[string]
  ✓ service_date: ISO8601
  ✓ provider_npi: string (10 digits)
  
  **Validation:** PASS ✓
end note

== Observability Injection ==

Gateway -> Observability : **4. Create Span**
note right of Gateway
  **OpenTelemetry Span:**
  {
    "trace_id": "trace-xyz-789",
    "span_id": "span-gateway-001",
    "parent_span_id": "span-001",
    "operation": "a2a_message_routing",
    "start_time": "2026-06-01T10:30:00.123Z",
    "attributes": {
      "source_agent": "clinical-agent",
      "target_agent": "benefits-agent",
      "message_id": "msg-abc-123",
      "priority": "NORMAL"
    }
  }
end note

Observability --> Gateway : Span created

== Message Routing Phase ==

Gateway -> Benefits : **5. Route Message**\n(to benefits-agent-1)
note right of Gateway
  **Routing Decision:**
  • Target: benefits-agent-1
  • Protocol: gRPC
  • Encryption: mTLS
  • Retry: Enabled
  • Timeout: 5000ms
  
  **Network Path:**
  clinical-agent-5.healthcare-prod.svc
    → istio-proxy (mTLS encryption)
    → istio-ingressgateway
    → benefits-agent-1.healthcare-prod.svc
    → istio-proxy (mTLS decryption)
    → benefits-agent-1 (port 8080)
end note

== Message Processing Phase ==

Benefits -> Benefits : Process Request
note left of Benefits
  **Benefits Agent Processing:**
  
  1. Validate input
  2. Query benefits database
  3. Check network status
  4. Validate service limits
  5. Prepare response
  
  **Database Query:**
  SELECT coverage, limits, network_status
  FROM benefits
  WHERE member_id = 'M123456'
    AND service_code IN ('97110', '97140')
    AND effective_date <= '2026-06-15'
  
  **Processing Time:** 180ms
end note

Benefits -> Observability : **6. Log Processing**
note left of Benefits
  **Processing Telemetry:**
  {
    "span_id": "span-benefits-002",
    "parent_span_id": "span-gateway-001",
    "operation": "validate_coverage",
    "duration_ms": 180,
    "db_query_time_ms": 120,
    "result": "COVERED"
  }
end note

== Response Phase ==

Benefits -> Gateway : **7. Send A2A Response**
note left of Benefits
  **A2A Response Message:**
  {
    "message_id": "msg-def-456",
    "correlation_id": "PA-2026-001234",
    "in_reply_to": "msg-abc-123",
    "source_agent": "benefits-agent",
    "target_agent": "clinical-agent",
    "message_type": "RESPONSE",
    "timestamp": "2026-06-01T10:30:00.350Z",
    
    "payload": {
      "task": "validate_coverage",
      "result": "COVERED",
      "details": {
        "service_codes": {
          "97110": {
            "covered": true,
            "network": "IN_NETWORK",
            "copay": "$25",
            "annual_limit": "$5,000",
            "remaining": "$4,200"
          },
          "97140": {
            "covered": true,
            "network": "IN_NETWORK",
            "copay": "$25",
            "annual_limit": "$5,000",
            "remaining": "$4,200"
          }
        },
        "provider_status": "IN_NETWORK"
      },
      "confidence": 1.0
    },
    
    "observability": {
      "trace_id": "trace-xyz-789",
      "span_id": "span-benefits-002",
      "processing_time_ms": 180
    }
  }
  
  **Response Time:** 180ms
end note

Gateway -> Clinical : **8. Forward Response**

== Audit Logging Phase ==

Gateway -> Audit : **9. Audit Log Entry**
note right of Audit
  **HIPAA Audit Log:**
  {
    "timestamp": "2026-06-01T10:30:00.350Z",
    "event_type": "AGENT_TO_AGENT_CALL",
    "source_agent": "clinical-agent",
    "target_agent": "benefits-agent",
    "action": "validate_coverage",
    "member_id": "M123456",
    "result": "SUCCESS",
    "response_time_ms": 180,
    "trace_id": "trace-xyz-789",
    "user_session": "session-789",
    "ip_address": "10.0.1.45",
    "compliance": {
      "hipaa_logged": true,
      "minimum_necessary": true,
      "authorized": true
    }
  }
  
  **Retention:** 7 years (HIPAA)
  **Immutable:** Write-once
end note

Clinical -> Clinical : Process Response
note right of Clinical
  **Response Handling:**
  
  1. Validate response signature
  2. Check correlation_id matches
  3. Extract coverage details
  4. Update workflow state
  5. Continue to next step
  
  **State Update:**
  state["benefits_result"] = {
    "covered": true,
    "network": "IN_NETWORK",
    "copay": "$25",
    "remaining_limit": "$4,200"
  }
  
  **Next Step:** 
  Proceed to parallel review
  (Clinical, Policy, Fraud agents)
end note

== Error Handling (Alternative Flow) ==

note over Clinical,Benefits
  **Error Scenarios & Handling:**
  
  **1. Timeout (>5000ms):**
  → Exponential backoff retry
  → Retry 1: Wait 1s, retry
  → Retry 2: Wait 2s, retry
  → Retry 3: Wait 4s, retry
  → After 3 retries: ESCALATE to human
  
  **2. Agent Unavailable:**
  → Gateway detects unhealthy replica
  → Route to healthy replica
  → If all replicas down: Return 503
  → Circuit breaker: Open for 30s
  
  **3. Schema Validation Failure:**
  → Reject message immediately
  → Return 400 Bad Request
  → Log validation errors
  → No retry (fix required)
  
  **4. Authorization Failure:**
  → Reject with 403 Forbidden
  → Audit log security event
  → Alert security team
  → No retry
  
  **5. Processing Error:**
  → Return 500 Internal Error
  → Include error details
  → Retry with backoff
  → Escalate after max retries
end note

